'''Henogamy''' is a [[norm (sociology)|social custom]] allowing exactly one of the children (or male children) in a family to [[marriage|marry]].

Henogamy typically exists in order to preserve family [[property]]. It is practised by the [[Nambudiri Brahmin]] [[caste]] in the state of [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2008 |title =Henogamy |encyclopedia=[[Encyclopædia Britannica]] |id= }}</ref>

