The '''Mole-Dagomba''' are a [[meta-ethnicity]] and western [[Oti-Volta languages|Oti-Volta]] Gur ethno-linguistic group residing in six present-day [[West Africa]] countries namely: [[Benin]], [[Burkina Faso]], [[Ghana]], [[Ivory Coast]], [[Mali]] and [[Togo]].<ref name="andani">{{cite book | title=The Abudu-Andani crisis of Dagbon: a historical and legal perspective of the Yendi skin affairs | publisher=MPC Ltd | author=Abudulai Yakubu | year=2006 | pages=152 | isbn=998803251X}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/33359-dagbon-celebrates-fire-festival.html | title=Dagbon celebrates Fire Festival | work=Graphic.com | date=6 November 2014 | accessdate=July 4, 2015 | author=Zakaria Alhassan & Samuel Duodu}}</ref><ref name="ghanaweb.com">{{cite news | url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Dagbon-first-encounter-with-the-white-man-323509 | title=Dagbon first encounter with the white man | work=Ghanaweb.com | date=30 August 2014 | accessdate=July 4, 2015 | author=Hardi, Ibrahim}}</ref>
